[0m[1G[0m[0m[?25h[38;5;141m> [0m{"verdict": "pass", "rationale": "The Python companion at chapter02.02-python-example.md uses correct boto3 APIs: bedrock-runtime Converse (with proper modelId/messages/system/inferenceConfig/guardrailConfig keys and correct response shape response['output']['message']['content'][0]['text']), comprehendmedical.detect_entities_v2 with correct Entities/Category/Attributes parsing, and DynamoDB resource.Table.put_item with Decimal conversion for floats. The five pseudocode steps (extract_critical_entities, segment_document, simplify_segment, validate_output, assemble_and_store) are each implemented with real logic and are tied together in simplify_clinical_document plus a runnable [1mmain[22m example that exercises the full pipeline on a sample discharge summary. Error-handling considerations are covered via comments (adaptive retry Config with rationale about Bedrock throttling, Comprehend Medical's 20,000-character limit, guardrail_intervened stopReason handling that returns source text rather than redacted output, DynamoDB Decimal requirement, and an extensive 'Gap Between This and Production' section enumerating ThrottlingException, chunking, retry loops, idempotency, IAM least-privilege, and VPC/KMS). No stubs: user-configurable constants (GUARDRAIL_ID, RESULTS_TABLE, MODEL_ID) are real values with graceful behavior when the guardrail is unset, and all functions contain complete implementations rather than placeholders."}